column2: create table SqlLog( --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- --/H a row for each distinct SQL record in the SQL Log.   ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- --/T See also the SqlLogAll view that denomalizes the table. -------------------------------------------------------------------------------  					sqlID		bigint identity(#,#) not null primary key,--/D unique identifier   					yy			smallint not null, --/D year 					mm			tinyint  not null, --/D month 					dd			tinyint  not null, --/D day (UTC) 					hh			tinyint  not null, --/D hour (UTC) 					mi			tinyint  not null, --/D minute 					ss			tinyint  not null, --/D second 					theTime	    dateTime not null, --/D timestamp 					logID		int not null, --/D id of server that generated record /R LogSource 					clientIpID	int		 not null, --/D id of IP address that generated record /R IpMap    					requestor   varchar(#) not null, --/D CasJobs, SkyQA, SkyServer, SkyDev, blank
